VIRAL MARKETING
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

Kazaa
http://www.kazaa.com/us/index.php
     Welcome to the post-Napster world. Wildly popular
file-sharing site Kazaa is a top 10 Internet destination
(note - it sometimes shows up under the "official" company
name of Sharman Networks). At the site, users download an
application called the Kazaa Media Desktop, which enables
them to share audio, video or other content files directly
using peer-to-peer (P2P) technology.
     While the entertainment industry continues to bemoan
this practice, early adopters like Microsoft are working
with P2P content packagers such as Altnet to distribute
copy-protected viral marketing content via the Kazaa
network. To combat the naysayers, Kazaa is promoting
the concept of an Intellectual Property User Fee (IPUF),
suggesting that a small fee could be added to ISP
subscriptions to pay artists and content companies for
use of their content.

