Google Viewer
http://labs.google.com/gviewer.html
     When you think about it, the concept of using a search
engine to find a website, reading a text description of that
website, and then clicking on its link to look at it (only
to repeat the process all over again if you don=92t like what
you see) is a bit tedious. Google to the rescue. The new
Google Viewer displays the pages found as a result of your
search as a continuous scrolling slide show, complete with
the text description framing the site=92s home page so you
can view it, click, or move on to the next.

